Ask students (or assist them) to write their name vertically down the left side of the paper using large letters. Then invite them to write a self-descriptive adjective or phrase for each letter in their name. Here's an example:

J—Jumps rope
U—Understands Spanish
L—Loves cats
I—Intelligent
E—Energetic


